===message:I agree with your statement about the propaganda used by the Soviet Union and the United States.  Both countries painted their own countries as "Superpowers" of the world.  Both countries depicted themselves as leaders in industry and agriculture.  I dont agree with the statement that soviet citizens envied american citizens.  They may have longed for more of the freedoms that Americans had in their everyday lives.  The little information the soviets received about americans was filtered in through the communist government.  As you stated, the soviets saw the prosperous lives of americans through propaganda, the lives only a few americans actually experienced.  The soviet citizens could not have been envious of the american way of life that did not really exist for all americans. 
